    "key": "497ca1f6-c5c4-4bda-9c5a-ebd73101e4da",
    "name": "Overview",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Overview",
    "content": "<p>In 2010, I graduated with a BSc (First Class Hons) in Human Nutrition and subsequently enrolled on an MSc in Applied Sports and Exercise Nutrition which I completed in 2011. Successively, I worked for two years in the health industry as a health and nutrition advisor for adults with autism and then as an exercise professional. In 2013, I decided to pursue a career in academia and conduct research on lifestyle interventions for healthy ageing. The opportunity appeared in the form of a scholarship offered by Queen Margaret University. I have been working at Queen Margaret since then.</p>\n<p>In 2014, I started working as a visiting lecturer while conducting my research projects. Since 2017, I have been working as an international moderator in Biosciences and Dietetics, a role that involves the facilitation of a quality assurance mechanism, on an academic level, between Queen Margaret and our collaborative partners. In 2018, I successfully defended my PhD thesis, and soon after, I embarked onto a course for exercise in Cancer Rehabilitation. I strongly believe in the importance of a healthy lifestyle, particularly diet and physical activity, which is a message I strive to put across during teaching and public engagement. My main pursuit is the augmentation of physical function, body composition and quality of life through nutrition and exercise interventions, with a particular research interest in healthy ageing and cancer rehabilitation.  </p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "81850437-e005-41a4-ad6f-eaea56dad76e",
    "name": "Research Interests",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Research Interests",
    "content": "<ul>\n<li>Sports and Exercise Nutrition</li>\n<li>Geriatric Nutrition</li>\n<li>Clinical Exercise Nutrition</li>\n<li>Sarcopenia, Obesity and Sarcopenic Obesity in Older Adults</li>\n<li>Dietary and Exercise Interventions for Healthy Ageing</li>\n<li>Lifestyle Interventions to Augment Body Composition and Physical Function</li>\n<li>Exercise for Cancer Rehabilitation</li>\n</ul>"
  },
  {
    "key": "f42b3366-39d5-4195-af75-ba6635ba94fb",
    "name": "Research Publications",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Research Publications",
    "content": "<p><a href=\"https://eresearch.qmu.ac.uk/browse?type=author&amp;value=Theodorakopoulos%2C+Christos\" title=\"Dr Christos Theodorakopoulos - eResearch Repository QMU\" data-anchor=\"?type=author&amp;value=Theodorakopoulos%2C+Christos\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Dr Christos Theodorakopoulos' research publications and outputs (QMU eResearch profile)</span></a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "f5150c2c-f93e-4ebc-bcb4-8640e4dff629",
    "name": "Teaching & Learning",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Teaching & Learning",
    "content": "<p>Subject areas: Introduction to Food and Nutrition, Nutrition, Exercise Nutrition, Body Composition Assessment Techniques, Epidemiology</p>\n<p>Programmes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>BSc (Hons) Dietetics; MSc/PgDip Dietetics</li>\n<li>BSc (Hons) Nutrition; BSc (Hons) Nutrition &amp; Food Science</li>\n<li>BSc (Hons) Applied Pharmacology; BSc (Hons) Human Biology</li>\n</ul>"
  },
  {
    "key": "af7ec7d3-d177-49f9-b324-29a5212e7076",
    "name": "Activities & Awards",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Activities & Awards",
    "content": "<ul>\n<li>2016: Princess Alice award (to present at the 2nd International Conference on Movement and Nutrition in Health and Disease, Regensburg, Germany)</li>\n<li>2016: Vice Chancellor’s award (to present at the European Society for Clinical Nutrition and Metabolism - ESPEN Congress 2016 in Copenhagen, Denmark)</li>\n<li>2016: Award for best scoring poster submitted from the UK to ESPEN Congress 2016 (Copenhagen, Denmark)</li>\n</ul>"
  }
